Methods - collection of statements that are grouped together to perform an operation. Method is declared under a class
 eg: public static void display() {
 }
 display() - method name
 void - method does not have a return type...does not return anything
 public - access modifier..method can be accessed anywhere
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a apex class:
Click Our name in right top corner in SF page - > Dev console - > Force.com platform opened in another window
File - > New -> Apex class
Type the below code:

 public static void display() {
  System.debug('Hello World'); // Displays 'Hello World ' on the screen
 }

File - > save
To run:
Debug -> open exec anonymous window -> Enter Classname.methodname(); ( Hello.display();)
Check in the log - > Debug only - > U will see the o/p.
